Proud Moment 💫

Finally sashed as a WBFF Diva Bikini Pro! I won my pro card last November at my very first WBFF show in Miami. And last night, I was sashed by my Mom. A proud moment for both of us!

It was always a dream to compete. Through a lot of hard work, dedication, discipline, consistency, and perseverance, I made my dream come true by becoming a Pro and part of the WBFF Family ❤️

Tomorrow I make my Pro Debut and I could not have made it here without my coaches @joshphillips_wbffpro and @stacewbffproposing, my mom and everyone who has supported me through this!

Let’s do this! ✨

12 months of progress! 💫

Results do not happen overnight! They take time, effort, discipline and consistency! As I trained for my WBFF Pro Debut, I learned so much about the process and about myself! Moral of the story, keep going. Don’t give up when things get tough! You’re stronger than you think you are! 🤍

Rang in the new year with amazing people and had the best night!

2023 New Year Goals 💫

✨Be kinder to myself - stop any negative self talk and comparing myself to others
✨Improve my physique - 2022 I brought my best physique ever to the stage, this year I want to have my best physique on and off the stage
✨Have more self confidence - stop doubting myself and be my biggest cheerleader
✨Train harder in the gym - progress won’t happen unless I push myself. Gotta be the hardest worker in the room!
✨Travel more -take more trips near and far! Make memories seeing and doing new things!
✨Take more action and hold myself accountable - stop only dreaming and start doing. Dreams won’t come true unless I put actions behind the thoughts. Only I can make it happen. 
✨Don’t stress over things I can’t change - this one speaks for itself 
✨Strengthen my mindset - read more, learn more and rewrite my brain
✨Earn and save more money - increase my income, learn about finances and investing, plan for my future so I can retire early
✨Grow my online fitness biz - not many know but I’m a certified personal trainer. I want to take on more clients to help them get fit, healthy and live better lifestyles. If this is you, send me a dm and we can chat! But will be promoting this more in days ahead! 
✨Do more of what brings me joy and happiness! - schedule out time in my days to do what sets my soul on fire. Life’s too short to not be living life joyfully

All part of the process 💫

Healing isn’t always 100%. It’s a process that we take at different speeds and routes. It is not linear. Over time, the hurt we once felt, lessens. 

People often forget that others are also in a healing process. They don’t know how far into that process that they are. They want to make judgements based on the surface rather than take the time to actually get to know someone. To learn how far they’ve come or the journey they’re on. Just because they “spazz” on you, it more than likely wasn’t intentional, but that your action (or lack there of) was a trigger. 

So next time someone “spazzes” on you, remember they might just be in different healing stage than you. Be understanding and be patient. You never know what someone might be going through.

Thank you for coming to my TED talk 🤍

Keep on, keepin on 💫

The side of me I never show. Some days it’s hard to get out of bed, but I remember why I have to. 

Doing things that bring me joy and make me feel good can instantly turn my mood around. Simple things like doing my hair and makeup, cleaning my apartment, getting out into the sunshine all make me feel good, even if I don’t feel like doing them at first.

Sometimes the weight of my thoughts gets too heavy, and I need to feel those feelings. I’m not afraid to cry or let it out anymore. Holding it in is scarier. 

I know the feeling will pass. I remind myself that I will be okay, and it’s all up to me to keep going. 

To keep on, keeping on. 💫

4am gym club ☀️

People ask why I go to the gym so early. Why don’t I just go later?  Well I’ve found that I really enjoy early morning workouts. It feels good knowing I’m getting my workout done before most people even wake up for the day. Getting it done early allows me to not stress about having to do it later, I have more time for life in the evenings and I don’t have to fight the evening rush at the gym. 

What works for me, might not work for you. And that’s okay! I’ll still be getting those early workouts in for me!

I choose me 🤍

Today. And all days. I give myself peace, love and happiness.

Happy birthday month to me 🥳

I don’t think I’ve ever done this but here are some super duper fun facts about me 💫

I’m 37, going on 38. But I really feel like I’m so much younger 

I’m a “since day 1 Swiftie” 🎶

My fave holiday is Christmas and I absolutely love Christmas music, at anytime of the year 🎄 

I’m a certified personal trainer

I have a Bachelor’s in Neuroscience 🧠 

I earned my pro card at my very first WBFF Bikini competition

I love to travel and want to see the world 🌎 

I wear my heart on my sleeve 🩷

I dream of owning my own businesses

I’m scared of spiders and growing old alone

I want to kiddos some day

I hope to find someone to do life with 💕

Each year I get older, I realize life is more about the meaningful connections, the small moments that are really the big moments, to tell those I love that I love them, that tomorrow isn’t promised and to live for the day, to take risks and don’t be afraid of getting my heart broke or of failing. Im growing, evolving and learning to love myself as I make my way through this crazy life. Here’s to another lap around the sun ☀️

2023 recap 💫

Not the best year, but certainly not the worst!

I learned a lot this past year. I learned to love myself, give myself grace, found my self worth, stepped out of my comfort zone. 

Im taking into 2024 the life lessons I learned to continue being the best I can. I will spend my time living and loving myself. To see and do all the things life has to offer. To stop being afraid to do things because I’m by myself. It was honestly a lonely year. But I got to experience some amazing things because I chose to step out and do them because I wanted to feel alive. Life doesn’t stop because we’re alone. I have the freedom to do what sets my soul on fire. 

In 2024, I plan to do so much more! The goals are big! Personal goal. Fitness goals. Business goals. Aallllll the goals! 💫

Goodbye 2023, thank you for everything. I’ll be forever grateful 🤍
Hello 2024 🥂
